sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_1ef626511b887b4066fe4225bd4bcbd3
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001203</definition_id><description>Count of Distinct CI in CMDB where Source is ALL</description><exec_time_threshold>10000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Monthly Count of Distinct CIs in CMDB [All Sources]</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = getUniqueCIAllSource();

function getUniqueCIAllSource() {
	var result = {};
	if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid('sys_object_source'))
		return result;
	
	if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid('cmdb'))
		return result;
	
	// Count of total CI's found
	var totalCICount = 0;
	
	// Generates the total unique CI count.
	// It is possible for a CI to belong to two different tables/classes; this
	// query counts unique CI sys_id
	var gr = new GlideAggregate('sys_object_source');
	gr.addNotNullQuery('target_table');
	gr.addNotNullQuery('target_sys_id');
	gr.addJoinQuery('cmdb', 'target_sys_id', 'sys_id');
	gr.addAggregate('count(distinct','target_sys_id');
	gr.setGroup(false);
	gr.query();
	if (gr.next())
		totalCICount = parseInt(gr.getAggregate('count(distinct','target_sys_id'));
	
	return totalCICount;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-03-07 00:09:13</sys_created_on><sys_id>1ef626511b887b4066fe4225bd4bcbd3</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001203</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_1ef626511b887b4066fe4225bd4bcbd3</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:37</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_5d4082c5dbf814149ee09a82ca96190c
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type>count</agg_type><count_type>Licensing</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1002993</definition_id><description>Unique users across all 4 safe workplace apps with meaningful benefit from at least one of the apps. </description><exec_time_threshold>5000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Safe Workplace User Count</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[var usrs = [];

//Requirement Document: https://servicenow.sharepoint.com/:w:/r/sites/crisismanagement/_layouts/15/doc2.aspx?sourcedoc=%7Bf062e680-74ef-4a02-8ac4-028dc44834ed%7D&action=edit&wdPid=72bb8e30

/*This function de-dups the array records*/
Array.prototype.unique = function() {
    return this.filter(function(value, index, self) {
        return self.indexOf(value) === index;
    });
};

/*Workplace Service Delivery*/
/*Check for plugin activation*/
if (pm.isActive('com.sn_wsd_core')) {
    this.getUsersForWSD();
}

/*Employee Readiness Surveys*/
/*Check for plugin activation*/
if (pm.isActive('com.sn_imt_checkin')) {
    this.getUsersForERS();
}

/*Employee Health Screening*/
/*Check for plugin activation*/
if (pm.isActive('com.sn_imt_monitoring')) {
    this.getUsersForEHS();
}

/*Personal Protective Equipment Inventory Management */
/*Check for plugin activation*/
if (pm.isActive('com.sn_imt_ppe')) {
    this.getUsersForPPE();
}

function getUsersForWSD() {
    /*active users with the workplace manager role */
    var graWSD = new GlideRecord('sys_user_has_role');
    if (graWSD.isValid()) {
        graWSD.addQuery('user.active', true);
        graWSD.addQuery('role.name', 'sn_wsd_core.workplace_manager');
        graWSD.query();

        while (graWSD.next()) {
            usrs.push(graWSD.user.sys_id + '');
        }
    }
}

function getUsersForERS() {
    /*unique users who were sent a survey in the last month + # users with the Outreach Admin role */
    var graERS = new GlideRecord('sys_user_has_role');
    if (graERS.isValid()) {
        graERS.addQuery('user.active', true);
        graERS.addQuery('role.name', 'sn_imt_checkin.checkin_admin');
        graERS.query();

        while (graERS.next()) {
            usrs.push(graERS.user.sys_id + '');
        }
    }

    /*Users in Table*/
    var checkInSysIds = [];
    var graERS2 = new GlideRecord('sn_imt_checkin_employee_check_in');
    if (graERS2.isValid()) {
        graERS2.addEncodedQuery('response_mode=Survey');
        graERS2.query();

        while (graERS2.next()) {
            checkInSysIds.push(graERS2.survey.sys_id + '');
        }
    }
    var graERS3 = new GlideRecord('asmt_assessment_instance');
    if (graERS3.isValid()) {
        graERS3.addEncodedQuery('metric_type.sys_idIN'+checkInSysIds+'^sys_created_onONLast month@javascript:gs.beginningOfLastMonth()@javascript:gs.endOfLastMonth()');
        graERS3.query();

        while (graERS3.next()) {
            usrs.push(graERS3.user.sys_id + '');
        }
    }

}

function getUsersForEHS() {
    /*users who had a screen performed on them in the last month + # users with Health Screening surveyor role + # users with Health Screening admin role */
    var graEHS = new GlideRecord('sys_user_has_role');
    if (graEHS.isValid()) {
        graEHS.addEncodedQuery('role.name=sn_imt_monitoring.monitoring_admin^ORrole.name=sn_imt_monitoring.monitoring_user^user.active=true');
        graEHS.query();

        while (graEHS.next()) {
            usrs.push(graEHS.user.sys_id + '');
        }
    }

    /*User in the Table*/
    var graEHS2 = new GlideRecord('sn_imt_monitoring_request_for_entry');
    if (graEHS2.isValid()) {
        graEHS2.addEncodedQuery('sys_created_onONLast month@javascript:gs.beginningOfLastMonth()@javascript:gs.endOfLastMonth()');
        graEHS2.query();

        while (graEHS2.next()) {
            if (graEHS2.requester != '') usrs.push(graEHS2.requester.sys_id + '');
        }
    }
}

function getUsersForPPE() {
    /*users who requested PPE in the last month + users who were assigned PPE in the last month + # users with PPE Admin role */
    var graPPE = new GlideRecord('sys_user_has_role');
    if (graPPE.isValid()) {
        graPPE.addQuery('user.active', true);
        graPPE.addQuery('role.name', 'sn_ime_ppe.ppe_admin');
        graPPE.query();

        while (graPPE.next()) {
            usrs.push(graPPE.user.sys_id + '');
        }
    }

    /*User in the Table*/

    var graPPE2 = new GlideRecord('alm_asset');
    if (graPPE2.isValid()) {
        graPPE2.addEncodedQuery('model_category=75908ac740201010fa9b1403d3d5b1f0^ORmodel_category=94c08ac740201010fa9b1403d3d5b128^assigned_toISNOTEMPTY^sys_created_onONLast month@javascript:gs.beginningOfLastMonth()@javascript:gs.endOfLastMonth()');
        graPPE2.query();

        while (graPPE2.next()) {
            if (graPPE2.assigned_to != '') usrs.push(graPPE2.assigned_to.sys_id + '');
        }
    }


    /*User in the Table*/

    var graPPE3 = new GlideRecord('sn_imt_ppe_ppe_assignment_log');
    if (graPPE3.isValid()) {
        graPPE3.addEncodedQuery('sys_created_onONLast month@javascript:gs.beginningOfLastMonth()@javascript:gs.endOfLastMonth()');
        graPPE3.query();

        while (graPPE3.next()) {
            if (graPPE3.assignee != '') usrs.push(graPPE3.assignee.sys_id + '');
            if (graPPE3.assigner != '') usrs.push(graPPE3.assigner.sys_id + '');
        }
    }
}
var usrs2 = [];
if (!usrs === undefined || !usrs.length == 0) {
    usrs2 = usrs.unique();
}

answer = usrs2.length;]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-05-14 01:51:03</sys_created_on><sys_id>5d4082c5dbf814149ee09a82ca96190c</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1002993</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_5d4082c5dbf814149ee09a82ca96190c</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:37</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Licensing</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001299</definition_id><description>This script collects the usage data for the itom_standard SKU</description><exec_time_threshold>100</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Collect ITOM standard SKU license usage data</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = getCount();

function getCount() {
    var gr = new GlideRecord('itom_lu_usage_account');
    var accounted_usage = 0;

    if (gr.isValid()) {
        gr.addQuery('sku_name', 'itom_standard');
        gr.query();

        if (gr.next()) {
            accounted_usage = parseInt(gr.getValue('accounted_usage'));
        }
    }

    return accounted_usage;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-04-01 11:03:38</sys_created_on><sys_id>508cad25dbec334020df9f5faa9619ad</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001299</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_508cad25dbec334020df9f5faa9619ad</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:37</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type>count</agg_type><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEF1000259</definition_id><description>Number of disctinct schedules for PPS Resources</description><exec_time_threshold>3000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>distinct_schedules_for_pps_resources</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = getDistinctSchedules();

function getDistinctSchedules() {
	var gr = new GlideAggregate('sys_user');
	gr.addActiveQuery();
	gr.addQuery('roles', '=', 'pps_resource');
	gr.addNotNullQuery('schedule');
	gr.groupBy('schedule');
	gr.addAggregate('COUNT');
	gr.query();
	
	var count = gr.getRowCount();
	
	return count;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-03-02 04:45:02</sys_created_on><sys_id>67eb56389355320064f572edb67ffbfe</sys_id><sys_mod_count>7</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEF1000259</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_67eb56389355320064f572edb67ffbfe</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:58</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_9f466d8cdb687f0020df9f5faa96193f
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001281</definition_id><description>Monthly Breakdown of 10 Slowest Average Pattern Execution Times in Current Build</description><exec_time_threshold>5000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Monthly Breakdown of 10 Slowest Average Pattern Execution Times in Current Build</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[/**
 * Monthly Breakdown of 10 Slowest Average Pattern Execution Times in Current Build
 *
 * Steps to Build JSON:
 * 1) Find all MultiPage Patterns and aggregate them
 *     (ex. "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server - MultiPage 1 of xx")
 * 2) Find Patterns that match any Patterns found in Step 1 and aggregate them
 *     (ex. "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server")
 * 3) Find the slowest average Patterns that are not MultiPage Patterns
 *     (i.e. Exclude anything found in Step 1 and 2)
 * 4) Add the aggregated MultiPage Patterns from Step 2 to the slowest average
 *     Patterns from Step 3
 * 5) Sort the list by slowest, splice it to 10, and add rank
 */

var build, rollUpEnabled, indEnabled;
var MULTI_PAGE_PATT = /(.+?) - MultiPage .+/;
var PATTERN_NAME_PATT = /Pattern Launcher: (.+)/;
var HORIZONTAL_PATTERN_SYS_ID = '4f64c6389f230200fe2ab0aec32e7068';

answer = JSON.stringify(buildSlowPatternJSON());

function buildSlowPatternJSON() {
	var result = {};
	var buildTag, buildDate;

	// Find buildTag
	var reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.buildtag.last');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		buildTag = reusedGr.getValue('value');
	
	// Find buildDate
	reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.builddate.last');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		buildDate = reusedGr.getValue('value');

	// Return empty result if build/version not found
	if (buildTag && buildDate)
		build = buildTag + '_' + buildDate;
	else
		return result;
	
	// Find rollup-by-build toggle
	reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.discovery.perf.metrics.rollup_by_build');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		rollUpEnabled = reusedGr.getValue('value');

	// Find Individual Metric toggle
	reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.discovery.perf.metrics.enable_collection');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		indEnabled = reusedGr.getValue('value');

	// If rollup-by-build exists, we try the rollup-by-build table
	if (rollUpEnabled)
		useRollUpTable(result);

	// Extra fields added to resulting JSON if populated
	if (result['count'] >= 0) {
		result['current_build_version'] = build;
		result['glide.discovery.perf.metrics.rollup_by_build'] = rollUpEnabled;
		result['glide.discovery.perf.metrics.enable_collection'] = indEnabled;
	}
	
	return result;
}

function useRollUpTable(result) {
	if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build'))
		return result;
	
	var arrayOfMappings = [];
	var multiPageMap = {};
	var stringOfMultiPagePatts = "";

	var multiPageGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build');
	multiPageGr.addQuery('build_version', build);
	// Only 'Horizontal Pattern'
	multiPageGr.addQuery('probe', HORIZONTAL_PATTERN_SYS_ID);
	// Get every unique MultiPage record
	multiPageGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name', 'CONTAINS', ' - MultiPage 1 of');
	multiPageGr.query();
	while(multiPageGr.next()) {
		// e.g. extract 'Pattern Launcher: Tomcat' from 'Pattern Launcher: Tomcat - MultiPage 1 of 14'
		var match = MULTI_PAGE_PATT.exec(multiPageGr.getValue('ecc_queue_name'));
		if (!match)
			continue;
		
		// Find all MultiPage patterns and aggregate them
		var probeTimeCount = parseInt(multiPageGr.getValue('probe_time_count'));
		var probeTimeAverage = parseFloat(multiPageGr.getValue('probe_time_average'));
		var patternName = match[1];
		if (!multiPageMap[patternName]) {
			multiPageMap[patternName] = {
				probeCount: probeTimeCount,
				probeAvg: probeTimeAverage,
				eccQTopic: multiPageGr.getValue('ecc_queue_topic')
			};
		} else if (multiPageMap[patternName])
			calculateAverage(probeTimeCount, probeTimeAverage, patternName, multiPageMap);
	}

	// Find the singular versions of the MultiPage patterns and aggregate them
	// (i.e. 'Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server')
	Object.keys(multiPageMap).forEach(function(key) {
		var singlePattGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build');
		singlePattGr.addQuery('build_version', build);
		singlePattGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name', key);
		singlePattGr.query();
		if (singlePattGr.next()) {
			var singlePattProbeCount = parseInt(singlePattGr.getValue('probe_time_count'));
			var singlePattProbeAvg = parseFloat(singlePattGr.getValue('probe_time_average'));
			calculateAverage(singlePattProbeCount, singlePattProbeAvg, key, multiPageMap);
			// Save pattern names to query out later
			stringOfMultiPagePatts += key + ",";
		}
	});
	
	var rollUpGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build');
	rollUpGr.addQuery('build_version', build);
	// Filter by 'Horizontal Pattern'
	rollUpGr.addQuery('probe', HORIZONTAL_PATTERN_SYS_ID);
	// Filter out MultiPage patterns and their singular counterparts
	rollUpGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name','DOES NOT CONTAIN', 'MultiPage');
	rollUpGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name', 'NOT IN', stringOfMultiPagePatts);
	rollUpGr.orderByDesc('probe_time_average');
	rollUpGr.setLimit(10);
	rollUpGr.query();
	while (rollUpGr.next()) {
		// e.g. extract 'Network Switch' from 'Pattern Launcher: Network Switch'
		var pattMatch = PATTERN_NAME_PATT.exec(rollUpGr.getValue('ecc_queue_name'));
		var pattSysId = getPattSysId(pattMatch[1]);
		if (!pattSysId)
			continue;
	
		// Get top ten average longest patterns minus MultiPage patterns
		arrayOfMappings.push({
			pattern: {
					name: pattMatch[1],
					sys_id: pattSysId,
					ecc_queue_topic: rollUpGr.getValue('ecc_queue_topic'),
					ecc_queue_name: rollUpGr.getValue('ecc_queue_name')
					},
			avg_time_ms: parseFloat(rollUpGr.getValue('probe_time_average')),
		});
	}

	combineMultiPattToArray(multiPageMap, arrayOfMappings);
	sortAndSplice(arrayOfMappings);
	addRanks(arrayOfMappings);
	
	result['avg_slowest_patterns_in_current_build'] = arrayOfMappings;
	result['count'] = arrayOfMappings.length;
}

// Function to combine averages
function calculateAverage(newProbeCount, newProbeAvg, pattName, pattMap) {
	var total1 = pattMap[pattName]['probeCount'] * pattMap[pattName]['probeAvg'];
	var total2 = newProbeCount * newProbeAvg;
	var totalNum = pattMap[pattName]['probeCount'] + newProbeCount;
	pattMap[pattName]['probeCount'] = totalNum;
	pattMap[pattName]['probeAvg'] = (total1 + total2) / totalNum;
}

// Queries for Pattern sys_id
function getPattSysId(pattName) {
	if (!pattName)
		return null;

	var pattGr = new GlideRecord('sa_pattern');
	pattGr.query('name', pattName);
	if (pattGr.next())
		return pattGr.getValue('sys_id');
	return null;
}

function combineMultiPattToArray(multiPatterns, theArray) {
	// Push the aggregated MultiPage patterns into the list
	Object.keys(multiPatterns).forEach(function(key) {
		var multiPattMatch = PATTERN_NAME_PATT.exec(key);
		var multiPattSysId = getPattSysId(multiPattMatch[1]);
		if (!multiPattSysId)
			return;

		theArray.push({
			pattern: {
					name: multiPattMatch[1],
					sys_id: multiPattSysId,
					ecc_queue_topic: multiPatterns[key]['eccQTopic'],
					ecc_queue_name: key
					},
			avg_time_ms: multiPatterns[key]['probeAvg']
		});
	});
}

function sortAndSplice(theArray) {
	// Sort by descending average time
	theArray.sort(function(a, b) {
		return b['avg_time_ms'] - a['avg_time_ms'];
	});

	// Take only the 10 slowest (first 10 elements)
	theArray.splice(10);
}

// Adds rank to each pattern for explicitness
function addRanks(theArray) {
	for (var i = 0; i < theArray.length; i++)
		theArray[i]['rank'] = i + 1;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-03-27 18:45:39</sys_created_on><sys_id>9f466d8cdb687f0020df9f5faa96193f</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001281</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_9f466d8cdb687f0020df9f5faa96193f</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:38</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type>count</agg_type><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001340</definition_id><description>Total number of users who have skill level associated</description><exec_time_threshold>500</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>User With Skill Levels</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[var gr = new GlideAggregate('sys_user_has_skill');
if(gr.isValid()) {
	gr.addQuery('user.active', true);
	gr.addNotNullQuery('skill_level');
	gr.addNotNullQuery('user');
	gr.groupBy('user');
	gr.query();
	answer = gr.getRowCount();
}
else
	answer = 0;
]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-04-17 19:18:00</sys_created_on><sys_id>8e17bd76db3c3f4020df9f5faa961900</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001340</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_8e17bd76db3c3f4020df9f5faa961900</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:57</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

	gr.addQuery('task.sys_created_onONLast month@javascript:gs.beginningOfLastMonth()@javascript:gs.endOfLastMonth()');

	gr.query();
	answer = gr.getRowCount();
}
else

]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-04-17 19:18:57</sys_created_on><sys_id>885735fedb3c3f4020df9f5faa961916</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001342</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_885735fedb3c3f4020df9f5faa961916</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:57</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001224</definition_id><description>Maximum IntegrationHub transactions in last 12 months for all scopes.</description><exec_time_threshold>5000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>ua_ih_usage_max_all</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[var aggregator = new IHUsageMetricsAggregator();
var sums = aggregator.getTransactionCountByMonth(false);
var maxCount = 0;
while (sums.next()) {  
  var currentCount = parseInt(sums.getAggregate('SUM', 'use_count'));
  if(currentCount > maxCount) 
    maxCount = currentCount;
}
answer = maxCount;]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-03-19 18:34:01</sys_created_on><sys_id>7ae61c29dbd83b003fcbe1d3ca9619bb</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001224</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_7ae61c29dbd83b003fcbe1d3ca9619bb</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:57</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_b446e1c4dbe4ff003fcbe1d3ca9619ea
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001280</definition_id><description>Monthly Breakdown of 10 Slowest Average Sensor Execution Times in Current Build</description><exec_time_threshold>5000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Monthly Breakdown of 10 Slowest Average Sensor Execution Times in Current Build</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[/**
 * Monthly Breakdown of 10 Slowest Average Sensor Execution Times in Current Build
 *
 * Steps to Build JSON:
 * 1) Find all MultiPage Patterns and aggregate them
 *     (ex. "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server - MultiPage 1 of 2",
 *      "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server - MultiPage 2 of 2" must be aggregated
 *      into one average)
 * 2) Find Patterns that match any Patterns found in Step 1 and aggregate them
 *     (ex. "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server")
 * 3) Find the slowest average Sensors that are not MultiPage Patterns
 *     (i.e. Exclude anything found in Step 1 and 2)
 * 4) Add the aggregated MultiPage Patterns from Step 2 to the slowest average
 *     Sensors from Step 3
 * 5) Sort the list by slowest, splice it to 10, and add rank
 */

var build, rollUpEnabled, indEnabled;
var MULTI_PAGE_PATT = /(.+) - MultiPage \d+ of (\d+)/;
var PATTERN_NAME_PATT = /Pattern Launcher: (.+)/;
var TOTAL_PAGE_PATT = /.+\+ (\d+)/;
var HORIZONTAL_PATTERN_SYS_ID = '4f64c6389f230200fe2ab0aec32e7068';

answer = JSON.stringify(buildSlowSensorJSON());

function buildSlowSensorJSON() {
	var result = {};
	var buildTag, buildDate;

	// Find buildTag
	var reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.buildtag.last');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		buildTag = reusedGr.getValue('value');
	
	// Find buildDate
	reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.builddate.last');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		buildDate = reusedGr.getValue('value');

	// Return empty result if build/version not found
	if (buildTag && buildDate)
		build = buildTag + '_' + buildDate;
	else
		return result;
	
	// Find rollup-by-build toggle
	reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.discovery.perf.metrics.rollup_by_build');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		rollUpEnabled = reusedGr.getValue('value');

	// Find Individual Metric toggle
	reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.discovery.perf.metrics.enable_collection');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		indEnabled = reusedGr.getValue('value');

	// If rollup-by-build exists, we try the rollup-by-build table
	if (rollUpEnabled)
		useRollUpTable(result);

	// Extra fields added to resulting JSON if populated
	if (result['count'] >= 0) {
		result['current_build_version'] = build;
		result['glide.discovery.perf.metrics.rollup_by_build'] = rollUpEnabled;
		result['glide.discovery.perf.metrics.enable_collection'] = indEnabled;
	}
	
	return result;
}

function useRollUpTable(result) {
	if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build'))
		return result;
	
	var arrayOfMappings = [];
	var stringOfMultiPagePatts = "";
	var multiPageMap = {};
	var aggregatedMultiPageMap = {};

	// 1) Find all MultiPage Patterns and aggregate them
	var multiPageGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build');
	multiPageGr.addQuery('build_version', build);
	// Look for Patterns with MultiPage
	multiPageGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name', 'CONTAINS', 'MultiPage');
	multiPageGr.query();
	while (multiPageGr.next()) {
		// Extract "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server" and "2" from
		// "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server - MultiPage 1 of 2"
		var multiMatch = MULTI_PAGE_PATT.exec(multiPageGr.getValue('ecc_queue_name'));
		if (!multiMatch)
			continue;

		var sensorTimeCount = parseInt(multiPageGr.getValue('sensor_time_count'));
		var sensorTimeAverage = parseFloat(multiPageGr.getValue('sensor_time_average'));
		var sensorECCTopic = multiPageGr.getValue('ecc_queue_topic');
		
		populateMultiPageMap(multiPageMap, multiMatch, sensorTimeCount, sensorTimeAverage, sensorECCTopic);
	}

	// 2) Find Patterns that match any Patterns found in Step 1 and aggregate them
	Object.keys(multiPageMap).forEach(function(key) {
		// Extract "2" from "Solaris Server + 2" (should be total pages)
		var totalMatch = TOTAL_PAGE_PATT.exec(key);
		// Skip if no match
		if (!totalMatch)
			return;

		var pattNameFromMap = multiPageMap[key]['pattLauncher'];
		var pattCountFromMap = multiPageMap[key]['sensorCount'];
		var pattAvgFromMap = multiPageMap[key]['sensorTotalAvg'];
		var pattTopicFromMap = multiPageMap[key]['eccQTopic'];

		// Skip if the pattern is void (due to inconsistent count across MultiPages)
		if (multiPageMap[key]['void'])
			return;
		// Skip if there is a mismatch in total MultiPage count for this pattern
		if (multiPageMap[key]['multiPageCount'] != parseInt(totalMatch[1]))
			return;
		
		if (!aggregatedMultiPageMap[pattNameFromMap]) {
			var singlePattGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build');
			singlePattGr.addQuery('build_version', build);
			singlePattGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name', pattNameFromMap);
			singlePattGr.query();
			if (singlePattGr.next()) {
				// Check for singular cases of the MultiPage pattern and aggregate
				var singlePattCount = parseInt(singlePattGr.getValue('sensor_time_count'));
				var singlePattAvg = parseFloat(singlePattGr.getValue('sensor_time_average'));

				var totalCount = pattCountFromMap + singlePattCount;
				var totalSensorTime = (pattAvgFromMap * pattCountFromMap) + (singlePattAvg * singlePattCount);

				aggregatedMultiPageMap[pattNameFromMap] = {
					sensorCount: totalCount,
					sensorAvg: totalSensorTime / totalCount,
					eccQTopic: pattTopicFromMap
				};
				// Save singular pattern names to query out later
				stringOfMultiPagePatts += pattNameFromMap + ",";
			} else {
				// If no singular cases exist, add the MultiPage pattern to the new map
				aggregatedMultiPageMap[pattNameFromMap] = {
					sensorCount: pattCountFromMap,
					sensorAvg: pattAvgFromMap,
					eccQTopic: pattTopicFromMap
				};
			}
		} else if (aggregatedMultiPageMap[pattNameFromMap])
			// If the MultiPage pattern is already in the map, aggregate
			calculateAverage(pattCountFromMap, pattAvgFromMap, pattNameFromMap, aggregatedMultiPageMap);
	});

	// 3) Find the slowest average Sensors
	// This includes Probes and all other Patterns that are not MultiPage
	var rollUpGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build');
	rollUpGr.addQuery('build_version', build);
	// Filter out MultiPage patterns and their singular counterparts
	rollUpGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name','DOES NOT CONTAIN', 'MultiPage');
	rollUpGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name', 'NOT IN', stringOfMultiPagePatts);
	rollUpGr.orderByDesc('sensor_time_average');
	rollUpGr.setLimit(10);
	rollUpGr.query();
	while (rollUpGr.next()) {
		var rollUpSensorAvg = parseFloat(rollUpGr.getValue('sensor_time_average'));
		populateArrayWithSlowestSensors(rollUpGr, arrayOfMappings, rollUpSensorAvg);
	}

	// 4) Add the aggregated MultiPage Patterns from Step 2 to the slowest average Sensors from Step 3
	combineMultiPattToArray(aggregatedMultiPageMap, arrayOfMappings);

	// 5) Sort the list by slowest, splice it to 10, and add rank and sensor information
	sortAndSplice(arrayOfMappings);
	addRanksAndSensorInfo(arrayOfMappings);

	result['avg_slowest_sensors_in_current_build'] = arrayOfMappings;
	result['count'] = arrayOfMappings.length;
}

function populateMultiPageMap(theMap, regexMatch, countOfSensors, averageOfSensors, topicOfSensor) {
	var patternName = regexMatch[1];
	var multiPageNum = regexMatch[2];
	// Superficial key used to match MultiPage records ex. "Solaris Server + 2"
	var key = regexMatch[1] + " + " + regexMatch[2];
	if (!theMap[key]) {
		// If the MultiPage is not in the map, add it
		theMap[key] = {
			pattLauncher: patternName,
			sensorCount: countOfSensors,
			sensorTotalAvg: averageOfSensors,
			eccQTopic: topicOfSensor,
			multiPageCount: 1
		};
	} else if (theMap[key] && !theMap[key]['void']) {
		// If the MultiPage is in the map and is not void, add it
		if (countOfSensors === theMap[key]['sensorCount']) {
			// Aggregate the sum of the sensor time
			theMap[key]['sensorTotalAvg'] += averageOfSensors;
			// Keep track of MultiPage Count
			theMap[key]['multiPageCount']++;
		} else
			// If sensor count is not consistent, void the multiPage Pattern
			// This is possible if bad data exists or manual manipulation of the
			// data occurs. Ex. If a sensor is run again but the ecc_queue_name
			// has been manipulated, that would yield bad data which we do not
			// care for.
			theMap[key]['void'] = true;
	}
}

// Function to combine averages
function calculateAverage(newSensorCount, newSensorAvg, pattName, pattMap) {
	var total1 = pattMap[pattName]['sensorCount'] * pattMap[pattName]['sensorAvg'];
	var total2 = newSensorCount * newSensorAvg;
	var totalNum = pattMap[pattName]['sensorCount'] + newSensorCount;
	pattMap[pattName]['sensorCount'] = totalNum;
	pattMap[pattName]['sensorAvg'] = (total1 + total2) / totalNum;
}

function populateArrayWithSlowestSensors(query, theArray, averageOfSensor) {
	// e.g. extract 'Network Switch' from 'Pattern Launcher: Network Switch'
	var pattMatch = PATTERN_NAME_PATT.exec(query.getValue('ecc_queue_name'));
	if (!pattMatch) {
		// If there is no match, must be a probe
		theArray.push({
			probe: {
					probe_name: query.getDisplayValue('probe'),
					probe_sys_id: query.getValue('probe'),
					ecc_queue_topic: query.getValue('ecc_queue_topic'),
					ecc_queue_name: query.getValue('ecc_queue_name')
					},
			avg_time_ms: averageOfSensor,
		});
	} else {
		// Must be a pattern if not a probe
		var pattSysId = getPattSysId(pattMatch[1]);
		if (!pattSysId)
			return;

		theArray.push({
			pattern: {
					pattern_name: pattMatch[1],
					pattern_sys_id: pattSysId,
					ecc_queue_topic: query.getValue('ecc_queue_topic'),
					ecc_queue_name: query.getValue('ecc_queue_name')
					},
			avg_time_ms: averageOfSensor,
		});
	}
}

// Queries for Pattern sys_id
function getPattSysId(pattName) {
	if (!pattName)
		return null;

	var pattGr = new GlideRecord('sa_pattern');
	pattGr.query('name', pattName);
	if (pattGr.next())
		return pattGr.getValue('sys_id');
	return null;
}

function combineMultiPattToArray(multiPatterns, theArray) {
	// Push the aggregated MultiPage patterns into the list
	Object.keys(multiPatterns).forEach(function(key) {
		var pattMatch = PATTERN_NAME_PATT.exec(key);
		var pattSysId = getPattSysId(pattMatch[1]);
		if (!pattSysId)
			return;

		theArray.push({
				pattern: {
						pattern_name: pattMatch[1],
						pattern_sys_id: pattSysId,
						ecc_queue_topic: multiPatterns[key]['eccQTopic'],
						ecc_queue_name: key
						},
				avg_time_ms: multiPatterns[key]['sensorAvg']
		});
	});
}

function sortAndSplice(theArray) {
	// Sort by descending average time
	theArray.sort(function(a, b) {
		return b['avg_time_ms'] - a['avg_time_ms'];
	});

	// Take only the 10 slowest (first 10 elements)
	theArray.splice(10);
}

// Adds rank and sensor info
function addRanksAndSensorInfo(theArray) {
	for (var i = 0; i < theArray.length; i++) {
		var sensorGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_sensor');
		var type;
		if (theArray[i]['probe']) {
			sensorGr.query('reacts_to_probe', theArray[i]['probe']['probe_sys_id']);
			type = 'probe';
		} else {
			sensorGr.query('reacts_to_probe', HORIZONTAL_PATTERN_SYS_ID);
			type = 'pattern';
		}
		sensorGr.next();
		theArray[i][type]['sensor_name'] = sensorGr.getValue('name');
		theArray[i][type]['sensor_sys_id'] = sensorGr.getValue('sys_id');

		// Add Rank
		theArray[i]['rank'] = i + 1;
	}

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update sys_domain="global" table="sys_script"><sys_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><abort_action>false</abort_action><access>package_private</access><action_delete>false</action_delete><action_insert>false</action_insert><action_query>false</action_query><action_update>true</action_update><active>false</active><add_message>false</add_message><advanced>true</advanced><change_fields>false</change_fields><client_callable>false</client_callable><collection>ecc_agent</collection><condition/><description/><execute_function>false</execute_function><filter_condition/><is_rest>false</is_rest><message/><name>Disable Pre-G Blocker BR</name><order>100</order><priority>100</priority><rest_method/><rest_method_text/><rest_service/><rest_service_text/><rest_variables/><role_conditions/><script><![CDATA[(function executeRule(current, previous /*null when async*/) {
	if (checkAllMidsUpgraded()) {
		var eccBrGr = new GlideRecord('sys_script');
		eccBrGr.addQuery('sys_id', 'IN', ['2450c0003702120069da03488e41f1d5', '210c00803702120069da03488e41f1e4']);
		eccBrGr.setValue('active', false);
		eccBrGr.updateMultiple();
	}
})(current, previous);

function checkAllMidsUpgraded() {
	var gr = new GlideRecord('ecc_agent');
	gr.query();
	while (gr.next())
		if (MIDServer.getByName(gr.name).isPreGeneva())
			return false;
	
	return true;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>will.swift</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2016-03-04 00:43:15</sys_created_on><sys_domain>global</sys_domain><sys_domain_path>/</sys_domain_path><sys_id>210c00803702120069da03488e41f1e4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>Disable Pre-G Blocker BR</sys_name><sys_overrides/><sys_package display_value="MID Server" source="com.glideapp.agent">8be6bad507c20010944dfc018c1ed065</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_script_210c00803702120069da03488e41f1e4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>system</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-30 07:35:58</sys_updated_on><template/><when>after</when></sys_script><sys_translated_text action="delete_multiple" query="documentkey=210c00803702120069da03488e41f1e4"/></record_update>

var sums = aggregator.getTransactionCountByMonth('sys_hub_step_instance', false);
var totalSum = 0;
while (sums.next()) {

}
answer = totalSum/12;]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-08-17 00:10:45</sys_created_on><sys_id>45892e36e7a0030007a64caac2f6a9d7</sys_id><sys_mod_count>8</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEF1000407</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_45892e36e7a0030007a64caac2f6a9d7</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:58</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type>count</agg_type><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1002224</definition_id><description>Number of shifts with Rotate through Roster Escalation type</description><exec_time_threshold>5000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Number of shifts with Rotate through Roster Escalation type</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = getRotateThroughRosterShifts();

/*
* Count the number of shifts with Rotate through Roster Escalation type
*/
function getRotateThroughRosterShifts() {
	var data = {};
	var rowCount = 0;
	var gr = new GlideRecord('cmn_rota');
	gr.setCategory('usage');
	gr.addActiveQuery();
	gr.query();

	while (gr.next()) {
		var gr1 = new GlideRecord('cmn_rota_roster');
		gr1.setCategory('usage');
		gr1.addActiveQuery();
		gr1.addQuery('rota', gr.sys_id);
		gr1.query();
		if (gr.use_custom_escalation == false && gr1.getRowCount() > 1)
			rowCount++;
	}
	return rowCount;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-09-30 21:12:26</sys_created_on><sys_id>3039c1d0db54c01020df9f5faa9619e2</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1002224</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_3039c1d0db54c01020df9f5faa9619e2</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:56</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

// Call CMDB API to do Identification and Reconciliation of current row
var cmdbUtil = new CMDBTransformUtil();
cmdbUtil.identifyAndReconcile(source, map, log);
ignore = true;

if (cmdbUtil.hasError()) {
        var errorMessage = cmdbUtil.getError();
        log.error(errorMessage);
} else {
        log.info('IE Output Payload: ' + cmdbUtil.getOutputPayload());
        log.info('Imported CI: ' + cmdbUtil.getOutputRecordSysId());
}

})(source, map, log, target);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_transform_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-05-18 08:08:44</sys_created_on><sys_id>3c0dff1edb301010bf211461399619f9</sys_id><sys_mod_count>0</sys_mod_count><sys_name>onBefore</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_transform_script_3c0dff1edb301010bf211461399619f9</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-05-18 08:08:44</sys_updated_on><when>onBefore</when></sys_transform_script></record_update>

var sums = aggregator.getTransactionCountByMonth('sys_hub_step_instance', true);

  totalSum = totalSum + parseInt(sums.getAggregate('SUM', 'agg_value'), 10);
}

gr.addQuery('sys_created_onRELATIVEGE@dayofweek@ago@30');
gr.addNotNullQuery('duration');
gr.query();
var durationInMins = 0;
while (gr.next()) {
	end = new GlideDateTime(gr.duration);
	durationInMins += parseInt(gs.dateDiff(start, end, true));
}
answer = Math.round(durationInMins / 60);]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-09-30 22:31:33</sys_created_on><sys_id>e34bd99cdb94c01020df9f5faa961950</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1002227</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_e34bd99cdb94c01020df9f5faa961950</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:57</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_819e10449319320064f572edb67ffb49
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEF1000262</definition_id><description>Minimum number of project funding records by portfolio and fiscal year</description><exec_time_threshold>3000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>1</license_model><name>min_project_funding_records_by_portfolio_and_fiscal_year</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = getMinProjectFundingCount();

function getMinProjectFundingCount() {
	var ga = new GlideAggregate('project_funding');
	ga.addAggregate('COUNT');
	ga.addNotNullQuery('portfolio');
	ga.addNotNullQuery('task');
	ga.groupBy('portfolio');
	ga.groupBy('fiscal_period.fiscal_year');
	ga.query();
	
	var minRecords;
	while (ga.next()) {
		var recordCount = ga.getAggregate('COUNT');
		if (!gs.nil(recordCount) && (parseInt(recordCount) < minRecords || gs.nil(minRecords)))
			minRecords = parseInt(recordCount);
	}
	
	return minRecords;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-02-27 11:36:22</sys_created_on><sys_id>819e10449319320064f572edb67ffb49</sys_id><sys_mod_count>6</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEF1000262</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_819e10449319320064f572edb67ffb49</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:39</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_c66e7bbab3020300176b051a16a8dc5e
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Licensing</count_type><definition_id>DEF1000420</definition_id><description>In the last 12 months, the highest Orchestration Core and IntegrationHub transactions executed in a given month</description><exec_time_threshold>300000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>1</license_model><name>MaxOrchAndIntegrationHubTransactionsLast12Month</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[function getOrchMaxCount(){
	var maxCnt=0;
	if(GlidePluginManager.isActive('com.snc.runbook_automation.runtime')) {
		// Last 12 months
		var queryString = "sys_created_onBETWEENjavascript:gs.monthsAgoStart(12)@javascript:gs.endOfLastMonth()";
		var monthlyTrend = new global.OrchCoreTransactionQuery().getTransactionsCountMonthlyTrend(queryString);
		
		for(var i=0; i<monthlyTrend.length; i++){
			var monthlyCount = monthlyTrend[i].count;
			var month = monthlyTrend[i].month;
			var monthlyQueryString = "sys_created_onBETWEENjavascript:gs.monthsAgoStart(" + month + ")@javascript:gs.monthsAgoStart(" + month-1 + ")";
			var sampCnt = new global.SAMPTXCounter().getReclamationTXCount(monthlyQueryString);
			monthlyCount = monthlyCount - sampCnt;
			if (monthlyCount > maxCnt)
				maxCnt = monthlyCount;
		}
	}
	return maxCnt;
}

function getIHMaxCount(){
	var aggregator = new OutboundUsageMetricsAggregator();
	var sums = aggregator.getTransactionCountByMonth('sys_hub_step_instance', true);
	var maxCount = 0;
	while (sums.next()) {
		var currentCount = parseInt(sums.getAggregate('SUM', 'agg_value'));
		if(currentCount > maxCount)
			maxCount = currentCount;
	}
	return maxCount;
}
answer = getOrchMaxCount()+getIHMaxCount();]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-10-30 20:00:06</sys_created_on><sys_id>c66e7bbab3020300176b051a16a8dc5e</sys_id><sys_mod_count>9</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEF1000420</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_c66e7bbab3020300176b051a16a8dc5e</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:59</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_72da9968db3b3b0020df9f5faa961953
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type>count</agg_type><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001987</definition_id><description> Number of requests with multiple RITMs in the last month</description><exec_time_threshold>1000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Last Month Requests with multiple RITMs </name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[var gr = new GlideAggregate('sc_req_item');
if(gr.isValid()) {
    gr.addAggregate('COUNT','request');
    gr.addEncodedQuery("sys_created_onONLast month@javascript:gs.beginningOfLastMonth()@javascript:gs.endOfLastMonth()");
    gr.addHaving('COUNT','>=',2);
    gr.query();
    answer = gr.getRowCount();
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-09-06 20:36:41</sys_created_on><sys_id>72da9968db3b3b0020df9f5faa961953</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001987</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_72da9968db3b3b0020df9f5faa961953</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:57</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_b17a2e36e7a0030007a64caac2f6a9df
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEF1000408</definition_id><description>Maximum transactions in last 12 months for all scopes</description><exec_time_threshold>5000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>outbound_usage_metrics_max_all</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[var aggregator = new OutboundUsageMetricsAggregator();
var sums = aggregator.getTransactionCountByMonth('sys_hub_step_instance', false);
var maxCount = 0;
while (sums.next()) {  
  var currentCount = parseInt(sums.getAggregate('SUM', 'agg_value'));
  if(currentCount > maxCount) 
    maxCount = currentCount;
}
answer = maxCount;]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-08-17 00:14:12</sys_created_on><sys_id>b17a2e36e7a0030007a64caac2f6a9df</sys_id><sys_mod_count>9</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEF1000408</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_b17a2e36e7a0030007a64caac2f6a9df</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:58</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEF1000421</definition_id><description>Orchestration Core and IntegrationHub transactions executed in last month</description><exec_time_threshold>300000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>1</license_model><name>OrchAndIntegrationHubTransactionsLastMonth</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[// Orchestration Transactions LastMonth
var orchTxLastMonth = 0;
if(GlidePluginManager.isActive('com.snc.runbook_automation.runtime')) {
	orchTxLastMonth = new global.OrchCoreTransactionQuery().getTransactionsCount("sys_created_onONLast month@javascript:gs.beginningOfLastMonth()@javascript:gs.endOfLastMonth()");
	// get SAMP TX and substract SAMP TX 
	var sampCount = new global.SAMPTXCounter().getReclamationTXCountForLastMonth();
	orchTxLastMonth = orchTxLastMonth - sampCount;
} 
// IntegrationHub Transaction LastMonth
var ihTxLastMonth = new OutboundUsageMetricsAggregator().getTransactionCountForLastMonth('sys_hub_step_instance', true);

answer = orchTxLastMonth+ihTxLastMonth;]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-10-30 20:08:48</sys_created_on><sys_id>67b180cbb3020300176b051a16a8dca4</sys_id><sys_mod_count>8</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEF1000421</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_67b180cbb3020300176b051a16a8dca4</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:58</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_9936e54cdb687f0020df9f5faa961968
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001279</definition_id><description>Monthly Breakdown of 10 Slowest Average IRE Execution Times in Current Build</description><exec_time_threshold>5000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Monthly Breakdown of 10 Slowest Average IRE Execution Times in Current Build</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[/**
 * Monthly Breakdown of 10 Slowest Average IRE Execution Times in Current Build
 *
 * Steps to Build JSON:
 * 1) Find all MultiPage Patterns and aggregate them
 *     (ex. "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server - MultiPage 1 of 2",
 *      "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server - MultiPage 2 of 2" must be aggregated
 *      into one average)
 * 2) Find Patterns that match any Patterns found in Step 1 and aggregate them
 *     (ex. "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server")
 * 3) Find the slowest average IRE times that don't include MultiPage Patterns
 *     (i.e. Exclude anything found in Step 1 and 2)
 * 4) Add the aggregated MultiPage Patterns from Step 2 to the slowest average
 *     IRE times from Step 3
 * 5) Sort the list by slowest, splice it to 10, and add rank
 */

var build, rollUpEnabled, indEnabled;
var MULTI_PAGE_PATT = /(.+) - MultiPage \d+ of (\d+)/;
var PATTERN_NAME_PATT = /Pattern Launcher: (.+)/;
var TOTAL_PAGE_PATT = /.+\+ (\d+)/;
var HORIZONTAL_PATTERN_SYS_ID = '4f64c6389f230200fe2ab0aec32e7068';
answer = JSON.stringify(buildSlowIREJSON());

function buildSlowIREJSON() {
	var result = {};
	var buildTag, buildDate;

	// Find buildTag
	var reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.buildtag.last');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		buildTag = reusedGr.getValue('value');
	
	// Find buildDate
	reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.builddate.last');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		buildDate = reusedGr.getValue('value');

	// Return empty result if build/version not found
	if (buildTag && buildDate)
		build = buildTag + '_' + buildDate;
	else
		return result;
	
	// Find rollup-by-build toggle
	reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.discovery.perf.metrics.rollup_by_build');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		rollUpEnabled = reusedGr.getValue('value');

	// Find Individual Metric toggle
	reusedGr = new GlideRecord('sys_properties');
	reusedGr.query('name', 'glide.discovery.perf.metrics.enable_collection');
	if (reusedGr.next())
		indEnabled = reusedGr.getValue('value');

	// If rollup-by-build exists, we try the rollup-by-build table
	if (rollUpEnabled)
		useRollUpTable(result);

	// Extra fields added to resulting JSON if populated
	if (result['count'] >= 0) {
		result['current_build_version'] = build;
		result['glide.discovery.perf.metrics.rollup_by_build'] = rollUpEnabled;
		result['glide.discovery.perf.metrics.enable_collection'] = indEnabled;
	}
	
	return result;
}

function useRollUpTable(result) {
	if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build'))
		return result;
	
	var arrayOfMappings = [];
	var stringOfMultiPagePatts = "";
	var multiPageMap = {};
	var aggregatedMultiPageMap = {};

	// 1) Find all MultiPage Patterns and aggregate them
	var multiPageGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build');
	multiPageGr.addQuery('build_version', build);
	// Only 'Horizontal Pattern'
	multiPageGr.addQuery('probe', HORIZONTAL_PATTERN_SYS_ID);
	// Look for Patterns with MultiPage
	multiPageGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name', 'CONTAINS', 'MultiPage');
	multiPageGr.query();
	while (multiPageGr.next()) {
		// Extract "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server" and "2" from
		// "Pattern Launcher: Solaris Server - MultiPage 1 of 2"
		var multiMatch = MULTI_PAGE_PATT.exec(multiPageGr.getValue('ecc_queue_name'));
		if (!multiMatch)
			continue;

		var ireTimeCount = parseInt(multiPageGr.getValue('ire_time_count'));
		var ireTimeAverage = parseFloat(multiPageGr.getValue('ire_time_average'));
		var ireECCTopic = multiPageGr.getValue('ecc_queue_topic');
		
		populateMultiPageMap(multiPageMap, multiMatch, ireTimeCount, ireTimeAverage, ireECCTopic);
	}

	// 2) Find Patterns that match any Patterns found in Step 1 and aggregate them
	Object.keys(multiPageMap).forEach(function(key) {
		// Extract "2" from "Solaris Server + 2" (should be total pages)
		var totalMatch = TOTAL_PAGE_PATT.exec(key);
		// Skip if no match
		if (!totalMatch)
			return;

		var pattNameFromMap = multiPageMap[key]['pattLauncher'];
		var pattCountFromMap = multiPageMap[key]['ireCount'];
		var pattAvgFromMap = multiPageMap[key]['ireTotalAvg'];
		var pattTopicFromMap = multiPageMap[key]['eccQTopic'];

		// Skip if the pattern is void (due to inconsistent count across MultiPages)
		if (multiPageMap[key]['void'])
			return;
		// Skip if there is a mismatch in total MultiPage count for this pattern
		if (multiPageMap[key]['multiPageCount'] != parseInt(totalMatch[1]))
			return;
		
		if (!aggregatedMultiPageMap[pattNameFromMap]) {
			var singlePattGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build');
			singlePattGr.addQuery('build_version', build);
			singlePattGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name', pattNameFromMap);
			singlePattGr.query();
			if (singlePattGr.next()) {
				// Check for singular cases of the MultiPage pattern and aggregate
				var singlePattCount = parseInt(singlePattGr.getValue('ire_time_count'));
				var singlePattAvg = parseFloat(singlePattGr.getValue('ire_time_average'));

				var totalCount = pattCountFromMap + singlePattCount;
				var totalIRETime = (pattAvgFromMap * pattCountFromMap) + (singlePattAvg * singlePattCount);

				aggregatedMultiPageMap[pattNameFromMap] = {
					ireCount: totalCount,
					ireAvg: totalIRETime / totalCount,
					eccQTopic: pattTopicFromMap
				};
				// Save pattern names to query out later
				stringOfMultiPagePatts += pattNameFromMap + ",";
			} else {
				// If no singular cases exist, add the MultiPage pattern to the new map
				aggregatedMultiPageMap[pattNameFromMap] = {
					ireCount: pattCountFromMap,
					ireAvg: pattAvgFromMap,
					eccQTopic: pattTopicFromMap
				};
			}
		} else if (aggregatedMultiPageMap[pattNameFromMap])
			// If the MultiPage pattern is already in the map, aggregate
			calculateAverage(pattCountFromMap, pattAvgFromMap, pattNameFromMap, aggregatedMultiPageMap);
	});

	// 3) Find the slowest average IRE that are not MultiPage Patterns
	var rollUpGr = new GlideRecord('discovery_perf_metric_probe_sensor_rollup_by_build');
	rollUpGr.addQuery('build_version', build);
	// Only 'Horizontal Pattern'
	rollUpGr.addQuery('probe', HORIZONTAL_PATTERN_SYS_ID);
	// Filter out MultiPage patterns and their singular counterparts
	rollUpGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name','DOES NOT CONTAIN', 'MultiPage');
	rollUpGr.addQuery('ecc_queue_name', 'NOT IN', stringOfMultiPagePatts);
	rollUpGr.orderByDesc('ire_time_average');
	rollUpGr.setLimit(10);
	rollUpGr.query();
	while (rollUpGr.next()) {
		var rollUpIREAvg = parseFloat(rollUpGr.getValue('ire_time_average'));
		populateArrayWithSlowestIRETimes(rollUpGr, arrayOfMappings, rollUpIREAvg);
	}

	// 4) Add the aggregated MultiPage Patterns from Step 2 to the slowest average IRE from Step 3
	combineMultiPattToArray(aggregatedMultiPageMap, arrayOfMappings);

	// 5) Sort the list by slowest, splice it to 10, and add rank
	sortAndSplice(arrayOfMappings);
	addRanks(arrayOfMappings);

	result['avg_slowest_ire_execution_times_in_current_build'] = arrayOfMappings;
	result['count'] = arrayOfMappings.length;
}

function populateMultiPageMap(theMap, regexMatch, countOfIRE, averageOfIRE, topicOfIRE) {
	var patternName = regexMatch[1];
	var multiPageNum = regexMatch[2];
	// Superficial key used to match MultiPage records ex. "Solaris Server + 2"
	var key = regexMatch[1] + " + " + regexMatch[2];
	if (!theMap[key]) {
		// If the MultiPage is not in the map, add it
		theMap[key] = {
			pattLauncher: patternName,
			ireCount: countOfIRE,
			ireTotalAvg: averageOfIRE,
			eccQTopic: topicOfIRE,
			multiPageCount: 1
		};
	} else if (theMap[key] && !theMap[key]['void']) {
		// If the MultiPage is in the map and is not void, add it
		if (countOfIRE === theMap[key]['ireCount']) {
			// Aggregate the sum of the IRE times
			theMap[key]['ireTotalAvg'] += averageOfIRE;
			// Keep track of MultiPage Count
			theMap[key]['multiPageCount']++;
		} else
			// If IRE time count is not consistent, void the multiPage Pattern
			// This is possible if bad data exists or manual manipulation of the
			// data occurs. Ex. If a sensor is run again but the ecc_queue_name
			// has been manipulated, that would yield bad data which we do not
			// care for.
			theMap[key]['void'] = true;
	}
}

// Function to combine averages
function calculateAverage(newIRECount, newIREAvg, pattName, pattMap) {
	var total1 = pattMap[pattName]['ireCount'] * pattMap[pattName]['ireAvg'];
	var total2 = newIRECount * newIREAvg;
	var totalNum = pattMap[pattName]['ireCount'] + newIRECount;
	pattMap[pattName]['ireCount'] = totalNum;
	pattMap[pattName]['ireAvg'] = (total1 + total2) / totalNum;
}

function populateArrayWithSlowestIRETimes(query, theArray, averageOfIRE) {
	// e.g. extract 'Network Switch' from 'Pattern Launcher: Network Switch'
	var pattMatch = PATTERN_NAME_PATT.exec(query.getValue('ecc_queue_name'));
	var pattSysId = getPattSysId(pattMatch[1]);
	if (!pattSysId)
		return;

	// Get top ten average longest patterns minus MultiPage patterns
	theArray.push({
		pattern: {
				pattern_name: pattMatch[1],
				pattern_sys_id: pattSysId,
				ecc_queue_topic: query.getValue('ecc_queue_topic'),
				ecc_queue_name: query.getValue('ecc_queue_name')
				},
		avg_time_ms: averageOfIRE,
	});
	
}

// Queries for Pattern sys_id
function getPattSysId(pattName) {
	if (!pattName)
		return null;

	var pattGr = new GlideRecord('sa_pattern');
	pattGr.query('name', pattName);
	if (pattGr.next())
		return pattGr.getValue('sys_id');
	return null;
}

function combineMultiPattToArray(multiPatterns, theArray) {
	// Push the aggregated MultiPage patterns into the list
	Object.keys(multiPatterns).forEach(function(key) {
		var pattMatch = PATTERN_NAME_PATT.exec(key);
		var pattSysId = getPattSysId(pattMatch[1]);
		if (!pattSysId)
			return;

		theArray.push({
				pattern: {
						pattern_name: pattMatch[1],
						pattern_sys_id: pattSysId,
						ecc_queue_topic: multiPatterns[key]['eccQTopic'],
						ecc_queue_name: key
						},
				avg_time_ms: multiPatterns[key]['ireAvg']
		});
	});
}

function sortAndSplice(theArray) {
	// Sort by descending average time
	theArray.sort(function(a, b) {
		return b['avg_time_ms'] - a['avg_time_ms'];
	});

	// Take only the 10 slowest (first 10 elements)
	theArray.splice(10);
}

// Adds rank
function addRanks(theArray) {
	for (var i = 0; i < theArray.length; i++)
		theArray[i]['rank'] = i + 1;
}
]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-03-27 18:45:15</sys_created_on><sys_id>9936e54cdb687f0020df9f5faa961968</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001279</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_9936e54cdb687f0020df9f5faa961968</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:38</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001194</definition_id><description>Get the counts for each type of cloud service account on the instance</description><exec_time_threshold>1000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Monthly Breakdown of Cloud Service Accounts By Datacenter Type (AWS, Azure, etc.)</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = JSON.stringify(constructCloudServiceAccountsJSON());

function constructCloudServiceAccountsJSON() {
	var result = {};
	
	if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid('cmdb_ci_cloud_service_account'))
		return result;
		
	if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid('cmdb_ci_logical_datacenter'))
		return result;
	
	var total_count = 0;
	var accountTypeCounts = {};
	
	var datacenterTypes = GlideDBObjectManager.get().getAllExtensions('cmdb_ci_logical_datacenter');
	for (var i = 0; i < datacenterTypes.size(); i++) {
		var datacenterType = datacenterTypes.get(i);
		accountTypeCounts[datacenterType] = 0;
	}
	
	var accountsGr = new GlideRecord('cmdb_ci_cloud_service_account');
	accountsGr.query();
	while (accountsGr.next()) {
		var accountType = accountsGr.getValue('datacenter_type');
		accountTypeCounts[accountType]++;
		total_count++;
	}
	
	result['cloud_service_accounts_by_datacenter'] = accountTypeCounts;
	result['count'] = total_count;
	
	return result;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-03-01 18:56:14</sys_created_on><sys_id>f86feb2b1b7b674066fe4225bd4bcb43</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001194</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_f86feb2b1b7b674066fe4225bd4bcb43</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:38</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type>count</agg_type><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEF1000258</definition_id><description>Number of PPS resource users having non-floating schedules</description><exec_time_threshold>3000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>non_floating_schedule_pps_resource_users</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = getNonFloatingSchedulesCount();

function getNonFloatingSchedulesCount() {
	
	var ga = new GlideAggregate('sys_user');
	ga.addActiveQuery();
	ga.addAggregate('COUNT');
	ga.addQuery('roles', 'pps_resource');
	ga.addNotNullQuery('schedule');
	ga.addNotNullQuery('schedule.time_zone');
	ga.setGroup(false);
	ga.query();
	
	var count = 0;
	if (ga.next())
		count = parseInt(ga.getAggregate('COUNT'));
	
	return count;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2017-03-02 05:19:11</sys_created_on><sys_id>42ce96789355320064f572edb67ffbf0</sys_id><sys_mod_count>5</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEF1000258</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_42ce96789355320064f572edb67ffbf0</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-01-29 16:51:58</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001222</definition_id><description>Monthly Query of Instance Configuration [Credentialless Discovery Enabled or Not]</description><exec_time_threshold>100</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Monthly Query of Instance Configuration [Credentialless Discovery Enabled or Not]</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = JSON.stringify(getInstanceConfigForCredentiallessDisco());

function getInstanceConfigForCredentiallessDisco() {
var result = {};
var PROPERTIES_TABLE = "sys_properties";

if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid(PROPERTIES_TABLE)) {
return result;
}

var PROPERTY_NAME = "mid.discovery.credentialless.enable";
var count = 0;
var arrayOfMappings = [];

function getCredentialLessDiscoveryMap() {
var resultMap = {};
var propertyTable = new GlideRecord(PROPERTIES_TABLE);
propertyTable.addQuery("name", PROPERTY_NAME);
propertyTable.query();
if (propertyTable.next()) {
count = ++count;
resultMap[PROPERTY_NAME] = propertyTable.value + '';
} else
resultMap[PROPERTY_NAME] = "";

return resultMap;
}

arrayOfMappings.push(getCredentialLessDiscoveryMap());
result['instance_config'] = arrayOfMappings;
result['count'] = count;

return result;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-03-19 07:46:02</sys_created_on><sys_id>2a924255db543b003fcbe1d3ca961911</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001222</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_2a924255db543b003fcbe1d3ca961911</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:37</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="sys_transform_script"><sys_transform_script action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><map display_value="DS2">ed685c69db381010bf21146139961988</map><order>100</order><script><![CDATA[(function runTransformScript(source, map, log, target) {
// Call CMDB API to do Identification and Reconciliation of current row
var cmdbUtil = new CMDBTransformUtil();
cmdbUtil.identifyAndReconcile(source, map, log);
ignore = true;

if (cmdbUtil.hasError()) {
        var errorMessage = cmdbUtil.getError();
        log.error(errorMessage);
} else {
        log.info('IE Output Payload: ' + cmdbUtil.getOutputPayload());
        log.info('Imported CI: ' + cmdbUtil.getOutputRecordSysId());
}

})(source, map, log, target);]]></script><sys_class_name>sys_transform_script</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>admin</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2020-05-18 08:12:17</sys_created_on><sys_id>07dd335edb301010bf211461399619e2</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>onBefore</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Global" source="global">global</sys_package><sys_policy/><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>sys_transform_script_07dd335edb301010bf211461399619e2</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>admin</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-05-20 08:51:23</sys_updated_on><when>onBefore</when></sys_transform_script></record_update>

sys_update_xml.name: usageanalytics_count_cfg_0117e219db08b3409ee09a82ca96191b
sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Usage</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001204</definition_id><description>Count of Distinct CI in CMDB where Source is Discovery</description><exec_time_threshold>10000</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Monthly Count of Distinct CIs in CMDB [Source Is Discovery]</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = getUniqueCIDiscoSource();

function getUniqueCIDiscoSource() {
	var result = {};
	if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid('sys_object_source'))
		return result;
	
	if (!GlideTableDescriptor.isValid('cmdb'))
		return result;
	
	// Count of total CI's found
	var totalCICount = 0;
	
	// Generates the total unique CI count.
	// It is possible for a CI to belong to two different tables/classes; this
	// query counts unique CI sys_id
	var gr = new GlideAggregate('sys_object_source');
	gr.addNotNullQuery('target_table');
	gr.addNotNullQuery('target_sys_id');
	gr.addQuery('id', 'Discovery');
	gr.addJoinQuery('cmdb', 'target_sys_id', 'sys_id');
	gr.addAggregate('count(distinct','target_sys_id');
	gr.setGroup(false);
	gr.query();
	if (gr.next())
		totalCICount = parseInt(gr.getAggregate('count(distinct','target_sys_id'));
	
	return totalCICount;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-03-07 00:09:42</sys_created_on><sys_id>0117e219db08b3409ee09a82ca96191b</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001204</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_0117e219db08b3409ee09a82ca96191b</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:37</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>

sys_update_xml.payload:
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><record_update table="usageanalytics_count_cfg"><usageanalytics_count_cfg action="INSERT_OR_UPDATE"><active>true</active><agg_col/><agg_type/><count_type>Licensing</count_type><definition_id>DEFN1001294</definition_id><description>This script collects the usage data for the ITOM visibility SKU</description><exec_time_threshold>100</exec_time_threshold><group_by/><license_model>0</license_model><name>Collect Visibility SKU license usage data</name><overridden>false</overridden><query/><reportable>false</reportable><run_scope>global</run_scope><schedule>Monthly</schedule><script><![CDATA[answer = getCount();

function getCount() {
    var gr = new GlideRecord('itom_lu_usage_account');
    var accounted_usage = 0;

    if (gr.isValid()) {
        gr.addQuery('sku_name', 'visibility');
        gr.query();

        if (gr.next()) {
            accounted_usage = parseInt(gr.getValue('accounted_usage'));
        }
    }

    return accounted_usage;
}]]></script><sys_class_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg</sys_class_name><sys_created_by>system</sys_created_by><sys_created_on>2019-04-01 10:57:22</sys_created_on><sys_id>581b2525dbec334020df9f5faa961931</sys_id><sys_mod_count>1</sys_mod_count><sys_name>DEFN1001294</sys_name><sys_package display_value="Usage Analytics" source="com.glide.usageanalytics">f163361907020010944dfc018c1ed052</sys_package><sys_policy>read</sys_policy><sys_scope display_value="Global">global</sys_scope><sys_update_name>usageanalytics_count_cfg_581b2525dbec334020df9f5faa961931</sys_update_name><sys_updated_by>developer.program@snc</sys_updated_by><sys_updated_on>2020-06-10 12:17:37</sys_updated_on></usageanalytics_count_cfg></record_update>
